ENTRY            33222   20260314   20260508   20260508       3222
SUBENT        33222001   20260314   20260508   20260508       3222
BIB                 15         41
TITLE      Measurement of 64Zn(n,2n)63Zn and 67Zn(n,p)67Cu
            reaction cross sections at neutron energies of
            17.10+/-0.82 and 14.98+/-0.81 MeV
AUTHOR     (R.Chauhan, R.K.Singh, N.L.Singh, M.Mehta, R.Makwana,
            S.V.Suryanarayana, S.Mukherjee, B.K.Nayak,
            K.Katovsky)
INSTITUTE  (3INDBDA,3INDGND,3INDTRM)
           (3INDIND) Netaji Subhas University of Technology, New
           Delhi
           (3CZRCZR) Brno University of Technology, Brno, Czech
           Republic
REFERENCE  (J,JRN,334,6521,2025)
FACILITY   (VDGT,3INDTAT) 14UD BARC-TIFR Pelletron Linac
            accelerator
INC-SOURCE (P-LI7) A natLi foil target with a thickness of
            7.8 mg/cm2 was sandwiched between two Ta foils. The
            front Ta foil, 3.2 mg/cm2 faces proton beam to protect
            Li foil from heating. The back Ta foil, 0.1 mm thick,
            was used to stop the proton beam.
INC-SPECT  The neutron flux is on the order of
            4.75244E+06 n/cm2/sec at 21 MeV and
            2.32823E+06 n/cm2/sec at 19 MeV
SAMPLE     The natZn foil (~265.3 mg/cm2), wrapped in 0.025 mm
            thick Al foil.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) The resolution of detector was 1.82 keV at
            1332 keV gamma-line of 60Co.
MONITOR    (13-AL-27(N,A)11-NA-24,,SIG)
DECAY-MON  (11-NA-24,14.997HR,DG,1368.626,0.9999)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) The uncertainties associated to measure
            reaction cross sections propagated from:
           (MONIT-ERR) Monitor cross section (<1%)
           (ERR-1,,7.) Counting rate (<6-7%)
           (ERR-2,,3.) Efficiency calibration (<3%)
           (ERR-3,,0.2) Self-absorption (<0.2%)
           (ERR-4,,0.1) Sample mass (<0.1%)
           (ERR-5) Gamma abundance (0.5)
           (ERR-6,,0.2) Decay constant (<0.2%)
CORRECTION Low energy neutron contribution subtracted.
STATUS     (APRVD) Proof-read by R.Chauhan (2026-03-23)
           (TABLE,,R.Chauhan+,J,JRN,334,6521,2025) Table 4
HISTORY    (20260314C) VT
ENDBIB              41
COMMON               1          3
ERR-5
PER-CENT
        0.5
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           48
SUBENT        33222002   20260314   20260508   20260508       3222
BIB                  3          3
REACTION   (30-ZN-64(N,2N)30-ZN-63,,SIG,,SPA)
DECAY-DATA (30-ZN-63,38.47MIN,DG,669.62,0.082)
SAMPLE     (30-ZN-64,NAT=0.4917)
ENDBIB               3
NOCOMMON             0          0
DATA                 6          2
EN         EN-RSL-HW  DATA       ERR-T      MONIT      MONIT-ERR
MEV        MEV        MB         MB         MB         MB
      14.98       0.81      153.3      0.103      91.12       0.78
      17.10       0.82      213.3       10.1      70.42       0.63
ENDDATA              4
ENDSUBENT           12
SUBENT        33222003   20260314   20260508   20260508       3222
BIB                  3          3
REACTION   (30-ZN-67(N,P)29-CU-67,,SIG,,SPA)
DECAY-DATA (29-CU-67,61.83HR,DG,184.58,0.487)
SAMPLE     (30-ZN-67,NAT=0.0404)
ENDBIB               3
NOCOMMON             0          0
DATA                 6          2
EN         EN-RSL-HW  DATA       ERR-T      MONIT      MONIT-ERR
MEV        MEV        MB         MB         MB         MB
      14.98       0.81      53.41       2.26      91.12       0.78
      17.10       0.82      41.12       3.40      70.42       0.63
ENDDATA              4
ENDSUBENT           12
